= Ordered Lists

Ordered lists display items in a numbered sequence.

== Basic Ordered List

. First item
. Second item
. Third item

== Ordered List with Title

.Ordered List: Steps to Follow
. Step one
. Step two
. Step three

== Nested Ordered Lists

. First level item
.. Second level item
.. Another second level item
... Third level item
... Another third level item
. Back to first level

== Ordered List with Multiple Paragraphs

. First item

  This is a continuation paragraph for the first item.

. Second item

  This is a continuation paragraph for the second item.

== Ordered List Starting at Different Number

[start=5]
. Item five
. Item six
. Item seven

== Ordered List with Mixed Content

. Item with *bold* text
. Item with _italic_ text
. Item with `monospaced` text
. Item with a link: https://example.com

== Ordered List with Nested Unordered List

. First ordered item

  * Unordered nested item
  * Another unordered item

. Second ordered item

  * More unordered items
  * And another

== Complex Nested Lists

. Level 1, Item 1
.. Level 2, Item 1
... Level 3, Item 1
... Level 3, Item 2
.. Level 2, Item 2
. Level 1, Item 2

